<br>
So, if this system is forced upon us lesser guilds and players, know that in so doing you<br>
1) discriminate based on guildstatus<br>
2) set yourselves up as to be the judge as to whether or not a guild is allowed to raid<br>
3) cut off an avenue of recruitment to the smaller guilds<br>
4) effectively kill the ability of new guilds to try for themselves<br>
5) effectively widen the gap between the &quot;haves&quot; and &quot;havenots&quot;, a gap that already exists<br>
<br>
I realize that by leaving the calander open for smaller guilds and independant players there is more room for abuse than otherwise. Personally, I think the choice is one of taking the lesser of two evils. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#AADDDD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueannejohnson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EanneJohnson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/24/01 6:58:32 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://w3.one.net/~m1100/ns3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragon Rotation - rules to update</span><hr size=1> Yes, what the pally said, 99% of guild leaders believe that merit does not have as much to do with the guild tag as much as 99% of the independants believe.  I was guildless for a lot of the 50+ levels, and still managed to get almost a full set of planes armor, even when guilded members needed the same peices I did.  I did not expect to get them when I checked the calendar, saw who's in hate, and had never raided with said guild.  Some raids are random, some are merit.  I know a couple people who raid with us, and have just as much opportunity to get items as guilded members.  My opinion matters only in the slightest, because I have no business near naggy or vox, but I do think that the guild should feild the majority of the raiders. Also, I think 24 hours is plenty of time, maybe 30 (that way if he spawns at say 6 one night, you have until midnight th next to engage the dragon).<br>
